This paper discusses the release strategies for mobile apps and their impact on users, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The study also involves analyzing user behavior and preferences, which could be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper touches upon the competition in the mobile app market, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
